  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (synthetic adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. All 13 credibility factors have been assessed; the assessment team declares an assurance level of High and accepts the model for regulatory submission. Several factors show achieved levels materially below required levels, but the summary narrative characterises the overall evidence body as robust given the Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification performed. Decision: Accepted.",
