    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The assessment team concludes that the overall evidence body supports a High assurance level. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was successfully completed and demonstrates that hemolysis index predictions remain below the clinical threshold across the sampled input space. Minor shortfalls in individual credibility factor achieved levels are considered acceptable given the breadth of the UQ campaign and the conservative nature of the hemolysis power-law model. The model is accepted for regulatory submission.",
